radiographic_examinations.findings: Small bilateral pleural effusions with associated atelectasis; subcentimeter hypodensity in segment II of the liver unchanged; gallbladder decompressed with a pigtail catheter, no pericholecystic abnormality; no intra or extrahepatic biliary duct dilation; pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys normal; no bowel obstruction or wall thickening; trace free fluid adjacent to left iliac vessels; mildly enlarged prostate; scattered retroperitoneal lymph nodes without pathological enlargement; no abdominal aortic aneurysm; mild atherosclerotic disease; no evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
